primaryData.textualContent: John and Caroline needed some money to go on a school trip. "How can we make some money?" they said to each other. "You could sell mandarins on the side of the road," called out their mother. Mum had some great mandarin trees and there was so much fruit they couldn't eat them all. So John and Caroline filled up a green bin with mandarins. "We should make a sign too with the price" they said. Soon they were out on the road and waving to the cars as they passed by. They told people that the mandarins would make great marmalade. They charged $2.00 per bag for the mandarins, and soon they had sold all the fruit. "Oh my goodness, we have made $24.00!" said Caroline. "Why don't we fill the green bin again and make some more money?" "Oh no," said John. "That's all we need for our trip. I'm tired, let's go inside and have a rest. Good idea" said Caroline." But let's do it again sometime!"
